    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-12-23T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-12-23T13:00:00-05:00" n="886"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d886">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.1928/481: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Panama</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Flexer</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Panama</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-12-23T13:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 23, 1935—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 8:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>177. Referring to Department’s telegram No. 65, Oct. 25, noon, and Legation’s
                    telegram No. 173, Dec. 19, 2 p.m., third meeting held this morning. Panamanian
                    delegates will study and report Dec. 26 on two alternative drafts of last
                    sentence of third paragraph of proposed note: <pb facs="1003" n="910"
                        xml:id="pg_910"/>
                    <list>
                        <label>(1)</label>
                        <item>Fixing commissary prices to vessels of “sea stores” at retail price to
                            employees with commitment to voluntary restriction of sales only in
                            respect to “articles of other classes”; and,</item>
                        <label>(2)</label>
                        <item>Fixing “sea stores” prices as above and applying surcharge of 25% to
                            “articles of other classes” without mention of voluntary
                            refrainment.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>It is learned that Panamanian delegates are seeking telegraphic instructions from
                    Alfaro.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Flexer</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
